definition.value: A 5-methoxyfurocoumarin that is psoralen substituted by a methoxy group at position 5.
A member of the class of imidazoles that is 1H-imidazole substituted at position C-4 by a 2-aminoethyl group.
An oxysterol that is cholesterol substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 17 and 20 (the 20S-stereoisomer).
A chondroitin sulfate in which the site of sulfation is carbon 6 of the N-acetylgalactosamine (GalNAc) sugar.

A branched amino hexasaccharide derivative that is beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc in which the mannosyl group is substituted at position 3 by a beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-[beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->6)]-alpha-D-Man group.
A glucocorticoid that is prednisone in which the oxo group at position 20 is replaced by a hydroxy group. It is a metabolite of prednisone found in human urine.
An inositol having myo- configuration substituted at position 1 by a phosphate group.
A glucocorticoid that is prednisone in which the oxo group at position 20 is replaced by a hydroxy group. It is a metabolite of prednisone found in human urine.
The amino disaccharide beta-D-ManpNAc-(1->4)-beta-D-Glcp phosphorylated at O-4 of the mannosyl residue.
